• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above JOHANNESBURG – The incoming Wits University’s SRC led by Economic Freedom Fighters Student Command (EFFSC) is expected to hold a media briefing. The briefing is expected to address the fees must fall campaign protests and the leaked fees commission report which the City Press claim to in possession of. READ: Fears that leaked fees report will spark campus unrest According to the publication, the 748-page report emphasizes that free tertiary education, as demanded by students since 2015, is simply not feasible for the foreseeable future. The EFFSC led SRC is calling for a national day of action to demand free education and the official release of the report immediately. Unrest has already flared up at some universities. eNCA